1. Open config/TRIGGERS.json and add this trigger entry:

{
  "name": "GitHub Events - StarkOracle & Collaboration",
  "watch_path": "/webhook/github",
  "enabled": true,
  "actions": [
    {
      "type": "agent",
      "job": "GitHub event received: {{body.action}} on {{body.repository.full_name}}. Details: {{body}}. Process and execute any requested tasks."
    }
  ]
}

2. Use the GitHub API to register a webhook on the repository. Use curl to make a POST request to:
https://api.github.com/repos/GH_OWNER/GH_REPO/hooks

With the following payload:
{
  "name": "web",
  "active": true,
  "events": ["issue_comment", "push", "commit_comment"],
  "config": {
    "url": "https://955e-34-45-177-168.ngrok-free.app/api/webhook/github",
    "content_type": "json",
    "insecure_ssl": "0"
  }
}

Use the GH_TOKEN environment variable for authentication (--header "Authorization: token $GH_TOKEN").

3. After successfully registering the webhook, output the webhook ID and confirm successful registration.
